commitResults.messageTitle: Add classes for redo and undo commands.

commitResults.messageBody:
Undo manager contains the actual mechanisms for undo/redo.
It has a list that stores the state history of the Intern Watcher.
Methods:
- commitState(): Saves current state in the history
- undo(): Restores the previous sate from history
- redo(): Restores the previous undone state from history

When the application first launches, a VersionedInternWatcher instance
will be created instead of a InternWatcher instance. This is to allow
the states to be saved in a list.

commitResults.messageBody:
undo/redo previously displays "Action has been undone" or "Action
has been redone".

Undoable actions now commit a message to show the action that was
changed. The message is stored as a string in an array list
commandHistory, tied to the watcherStateList with the
currStatePointer. When undo/redo is called, the message is displayed
in the command result.
